Jabiluka to Energy Resources of Australia, which operates the nearby Ranger
uranium mine.
Mr Lindsay MacAlister, managing director, said the group had offset reduced
earnings from mining operations by cost-cutting and a fall in interest
payments. Net debt fell ADollars 48m to ADollars 173m.
Pancontinental shares have risen strongly in recent months, and yesterday
gained 5 cents to 96 cents on the Australian Stock Exchange.
