stay in Paris of the Palestinian radical, Mr George Habash, Reuter reports
from Paris.
The Communist party said before the vote it would not support the motion,
ensuring the survival of Mrs Edith Cresson's minority Socialist-led
government. The motion finally mustered 261 votes in favour, 28 short of
what it needed to succeed.
