a giant new national library in the centre of Paris which critics had
condemned as too grandiose, Reuter reports.
He said in a letter to Mr Jack Lang, culture minister, he had decided to
change the design after studying an independent report on the FFr7.2b
(Pounds 730m) project. The building would be made more cost-effective and
compact by reducing the height of glass towers to be situated at each of its
four corners.
