<HEADLINE>
FT  12 FEB 92 / UK Company News: Pounds 57,000 first half deficit at Elbief
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Despite an upturn in the second quarter Elbief ran into a loss of Pounds
57,000 for the half year ended October 31 1991, and is passing the interim
dividend.
Sales of the Elite range of clocks, mirrors and photoframes had varying
fortunes; the US was badly hit by recession but Europe and other export
markets increased. Sales of handbag frames continued to decrease.
Overall, turnover dropped 8 per cent to Pounds 2.27m after being 27 per cent
down in the opening three months. Despite cutting overheads and other cost
savings, the group was unable to avoid the loss, which compared with a
profit of Pounds 55,000 previously.
Losses per share worked through at 0.04p. Last year there were earnings of
0.043p from which an interim dividend of 0.181p was paid.
