<TEXT>
A HUNG parliament would result in a deterioration in the property market,
according to a poll of banks and financial institutions, Vanessa Houlder
writes.
Many lenders also felt that a Labour government would impede recovery,
according to the survey by Chesterton Financial, a property adviser, and
Thames Polytechnic.
Of the lenders surveyed, 58 per cent expected the market to deteriorate if
there was a hung parliament, 41 per cent thought that would be the case if
there was a Labour victory and 4 per cent saw a deterioration under the
Conservatives. The expected timing of a recovery was up to three years.
