FT  11 FEB 92 / Colour of money
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Colour of money: Royal Mail is breaking new ground with next month's issue
of four stamps ranging from Pounds 1 to Pounds 5. The Queen's head in the
corner of the stamps will change colour from gold to green depending on how
the light hits it. The effect is similar to the changing image on credit and
cheque guarantee card holograms, but is created by the first use on stamps
of a special ink which leaves a microscopically three-dimensional surface.
The ink has previously been used only when printing special documents and
foreign banknotes with a value of about Pounds 1,000. The aim, says Royal
Mail, is to deter would-be forgers, although there have been no signs yet of
such attempts. The stamps will be on sale from March 24.
</TEXT>
